columns.name: name
columns.description: A unique name to identify the cache policy.

columns.name: id
columns.description: The unique identifier for the cache policy.

columns.name: comment
columns.description: A comment to describe the cache policy.

columns.name: default_ttl
columns.description: The default amount of time, in seconds, that you want objects to stay in the CloudFront cache before CloudFront sends another request to the origin to see if the object has been updated.

columns.name: etag
columns.description: The current version of the cache policy.

columns.name: max_ttl
columns.description: The maximum amount of time, in seconds, that you want objects to stay in the CloudFront cache before CloudFront sends another request to the origin to see if the object has been updated.

columns.name: min_ttl
columns.description: The minimum amount of time, in seconds, that you want objects to stay in the CloudFront cache before CloudFront sends another request to the origin to see if the object has been updated.

columns.name: last_modified_time
columns.description: The date and time when the cache policy was last modified.

columns.name: parameters_in_cache_key_and_forwarded_to_origin
columns.description: The HTTP headers, cookies, and URL query strings to include in the cache key. The values included in the cache key are automatically included in requests that CloudFront sends to the origin.
